\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. C. communis} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 40 (1753). Subglabrous annual, with procumbent to ascending stems up to 70 cm. Leaves 5-7 cm, ovate-lanceolate, acute, ciliate at mouth of sheath. Cymes subtended by a large, keeled, spathe-like bract. Sepals ovate, membranous, 2 of them partly united. 2 larger petals bright blue, with suborbicular limb and narrow claw, the third much smaller, ovate-lanceolate, white. Seeds usually 4 (one loculus of the ovary being sterile), rugose.{\i  Naturalized in S. & C. Europe.} [Cz He It Ju Rm Rs (C, W).] ({\i Temperate Asia.})
