\pard\f0\fs28 Monoecious herbs, usually perennial. Leaves linear, usually in rosettes. Flowers small, numerous, 2- or 3-merous, in compact, bracteate capitula, the female near the outside, the male mainly near the centre. Perianth usually of 2 whorls, more or less glumaceous. Ovary superior, 2- or 3-locular, with 1 ovule in each loculus; stigmas 2-3. Fruit a loculicidal capsule.
